    "By using the preference datasets and the parameterized critic in Equation (9), we have the following InfoPO objective on preference pairs:",
    "Intuitively, the first term pushes the model to minimize the negative log-likelihood (NLL) of the chosen response, while the second term decreases the likelihood of the rejected response.",
    "The key contribution behind InfoPO is rather simple yet effective: If the gradients of both chosen and rejected responses lie on the same scale, we can prevent the reward (likelihood) of chosen responses from continually decreasing.",
    "InfoPO utilizes an exponential operation to linearize gradients on rejected responses.",
    "For comparison, we calculate the gradient of InfoPO with respect to θ using Equation (13):"
  ],
